						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Food-security/Related-developments/A-new-approach-to-accelerate-value-addition-in-Africa" title="A new approach to accelerate value addition in Africa" alt="link">A new approach to accelerate value addition in Africa</a></h2>

	
					<p>This article looks into why so many countries in Africa have to import agricultural products, mostly processed, while the same countries actually supply surplus quantities of the raw materials that are processed elsewhere. It explains how policy reforms would need to focus first on regional urban markets and demand to successfully tackle this aberration. The author calls for innovation and growth at the processing segment of the value chain: infrastructure, processing and packaging for local distribution, more consistent quantity and quality of raw agricultural products. It also discusses the role of the Agribusiness Innovation Centres (AICs) set up by the World Bank, that provide growth-oriented entrepreneurs with a holistic service offering.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://www.thisisafricaonline.com/Policy/Accelerating-value-addition?ct=true" target="_blank">http://www.thisisafricaonline.com/Policy/Accelerating-value-addition?ct=true </a>(This Is Africa, 8/01/2013)</p>
							<p><span class="date">7/03/2013</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Food-security/Related-developments/A-new-approach-to-accelerate-value-addition-in-Africa">Read more...</a>
</div>
